                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18120115-100-victim987 t18120115-100-viclabel591"></join>, I keep the <placeName id="t18120115-100-crimeloc592">Nag's Head, Tower Hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18120115-100-crimeloc592" type="placeName" value="Nag's Head, Tower Hill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18120115-100-crimeloc592" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18120115-100-off589 t18120115-100-crimeloc592"></join>, I lost the shirt in my own room on Tuesday last. A man came to me and asked me if I had not a coloured man in my house, I said yes, he opened a bundle and said, do you know that shirt, I said yes, he said the black man brought him the shirt.</p>
               <p>MR. MOSELEY. I am a slop seller in East Smithfield. Last Tuesday the prisoner came to the shop, he said, can you get me a birth, I said yes, I would send the captain to him. In about an hour after he came and said, will you buy a shirt, I said, let me look at it, I looked at it and saw I. G. marked on it, I told him he must go with me to Mr. Gibson, he then said he did not steal it, a man stole it and gave it him to sell.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I have been twenty-six years in the British service, and if I had not been in liquor I should not have done it.</p>
               <p>
